BFN 

  [Text] Macao, May 21 (XINHUA) -- China and Portugal have 
reached a consensus on Macao's accession to the International 
Association of Lighthouse Authorities, according to sources from 
the Chinese team of the Sino-Portuguese Joint Liaison Group. 
  The sources said that a formal agreement is expected to be 
signed at the 20th meeting of the Joint Liaison Group, scheduled 
to be held in Lisbon in July this year. 
  At a special working committee meeting Friday [20 May], 
representatives from both sides of the Joint Liaison Group also 
discussed Macao's accession to the United Nations Educational, 
Scientific and Cultural Organization (UNESCO) and both sides 
were optimistic to reach a consensus on this issue very soon. 
  The sources also said that the Chinese side has asked its 
Portuguese counterpart to give a name list of the international 
organizations, into which Macao has or wishes to join, for the 
purpose of helping smooth development of concerned work. 
  As for other issues, such as the involvement of Bank of 
China 
in issuing bank notes in Macao, preparations are going on 
smoothly and discussions on this issue are going to be held at a 
special meeting in early June. 

